1
00:00:26,945 --> 00:00:28,113
Aemie, stay here.

2
00:00:28,113 --> 00:00:28,822
Stay low.

3
00:00:28,822 --> 00:00:29,323
Huh?

4
00:00:29,323 --> 00:00:29,948
Stay low.

5
00:00:29,948 --> 00:00:30,616
Why?

6
00:00:30,616 --> 00:00:32,398
Music hits better when
you're ducking down.

7
00:00:45,673 --> 00:00:46,976
What's taking Zeke so long?!

8
00:00:47,007 --> 00:00:49,510
I look like an idiot sitting here
listening to music by myself!

9
00:01:05,526 --> 00:01:07,861
Zeke, why is there
so much blood?

10
00:01:12,157 --> 00:01:14,118
Please, I don't know what to do.

11
00:01:14,576 --> 00:01:16,245
Don't leave me, please!

12
00:01:17,204 --> 00:01:18,956
Don't leave me!

13
00:01:19,206 --> 00:01:20,265
So...

14
00:01:20,666 --> 00:01:22,167
What about the third target?

15
00:01:22,751 --> 00:01:24,169
You have to kill
her as well, Young.

16
00:01:24,294 --> 00:01:25,963
You really love
your husband, huh?

17
00:01:26,255 --> 00:01:27,589
Love him so much?

18
00:01:29,425 --> 00:01:30,759
How do you know that?

19
00:01:32,594 --> 00:01:33,345
Ouch!

20
00:01:33,345 --> 00:01:36,890
I found that to be
the safest and most suitable way

21
00:01:36,890 --> 00:01:41,395
to put a distance between
you and my husband.

22
00:01:41,520 --> 00:01:42,479
I love him.

23
00:01:43,689 --> 00:01:45,441
And I always will.

24
00:01:45,816 --> 00:01:48,986
I think we need
to remove all of this trash.

25
00:01:48,986 --> 00:01:49,611
Yuck!

26
00:01:50,154 --> 00:01:51,029
Okay, listen.

27
00:01:51,155 --> 00:01:54,241
I'll tell you the signs
that you're in love, okay?

28
00:01:55,242 --> 00:01:56,785
Okay, okay, okay, okay.

29
00:02:04,042 --> 00:02:05,169
<i>This is the first sign.</i>

30
00:02:05,294 --> 00:02:06,795
<i>When you get a strange feeling</i>

31
00:02:06,795 --> 00:02:08,505
<i>whenever he gets close to you
or stands near you.</i>

32
00:02:13,886 --> 00:02:14,803
<i>That means...</i>

33
00:02:15,471 --> 00:02:16,659
<i>you're already in love.</i>

34
00:02:27,191 --> 00:02:28,525
Come on, let's eat.

35
00:02:29,651 --> 00:02:31,153
Why are you stuttering, wife?

36
00:02:32,279 --> 00:02:34,323
Is something wrong?

37
00:02:36,283 --> 00:02:37,409
No, nothing.

38
00:02:37,618 --> 00:02:38,744
I'm just hungry.

39
00:02:40,788 --> 00:02:41,330
Come on.

40
00:03:37,594 --> 00:03:38,652
Uh.

41
00:03:39,888 --> 00:03:40,931
Hubby, so...

42
00:03:41,765 --> 00:03:44,059
so Fiona is your girlfriend?

43
00:03:45,769 --> 00:03:46,495
Hey.

44
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:47,813
Oh no, are you okay?

45
00:03:49,523 --> 00:03:51,108
You used to choke
on coffee only.

46
00:03:51,108 --> 00:03:52,401
Now, even on water?

47
00:03:57,406 --> 00:04:00,325
Fiona was my girlfriend.

48
00:04:06,248 --> 00:04:07,249
It's just...

49
00:04:08,625 --> 00:04:12,588
when she came to
the hospital, she said...

50
00:04:13,463 --> 00:04:15,173
she's still your girlfriend.

51
00:04:16,133 --> 00:04:17,134
What, she was there?

52
00:04:18,510 --> 00:04:20,095
Did she do anything to you?

53
00:04:20,888 --> 00:04:21,682
Ugh.

54
00:04:25,183 --> 00:04:26,111
No.

55
00:04:26,727 --> 00:04:28,061
She was actually nice.

56
00:04:28,896 --> 00:04:30,898
She even offered
to take care of you.

57
00:04:33,775 --> 00:04:34,735
Did you let her?

58
00:04:36,153 --> 00:04:37,362
Of course not.

59
00:04:46,872 --> 00:04:47,728
Huh!

60
00:04:48,707 --> 00:04:49,875
You bitch!

61
00:04:50,834 --> 00:04:51,668
<i>Second,</i>

62
00:04:52,002 --> 00:04:54,796
<i>If you get annoyed
every time you see</i>

63
00:04:54,796 --> 00:04:57,174
<i>another girl approaching </i>
<i>or talking to him...</i>

64
00:04:57,883 --> 00:04:58,842
<i>that's it!</i>

65
00:05:00,177 --> 00:05:01,553
Could that really be it?

66
00:05:04,097 --> 00:05:06,433
Am I really in love with Zeke?

67
00:05:37,547 --> 00:05:38,507
Woman!

68
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:39,967
Hurry up!

69
00:05:41,009 --> 00:05:42,678
Why are you in such a rush?

70
00:05:43,387 --> 00:05:45,222
It's only 6 a.m.

71
00:05:46,473 --> 00:05:47,933
He's just like cuz.

72
00:06:22,801 --> 00:06:24,219
Wait a second, Dong.

73
00:06:24,344 --> 00:06:25,387
Go downstairs first.

74
00:06:25,637 --> 00:06:26,596
I'll just get dressed.

75
00:06:28,140 --> 00:06:29,182
Okay, okay.

76
00:06:32,686 --> 00:06:33,770
What happened to him?

77
00:06:34,187 --> 00:06:35,439
Why is he suddenly blushing?

78
00:06:37,816 --> 00:06:38,358
Oh no.

79
00:06:39,443 --> 00:06:41,319
Do I need to take him
back to the hospital?

80
00:06:43,238 --> 00:06:45,741
What if something
happens to him again?

81
00:06:48,452 --> 00:06:49,244
Zeke!

82
00:06:49,244 --> 00:06:50,078
Zeke, wait.

83
00:06:55,292 --> 00:06:56,268
Zeke!

84
00:06:56,293 --> 00:06:57,198
Zeke!

85
00:06:58,086 --> 00:06:59,292
Help!

86
00:06:59,463 --> 00:07:00,756
Please, help!

87
00:07:08,889 --> 00:07:09,964
What's the matter?

88
00:07:16,104 --> 00:07:17,272
You don't want a ride?

89
00:07:18,690 --> 00:07:20,108
You want to walk?

90
00:07:22,486 --> 00:07:23,945
Well...

91
00:07:33,121 --> 00:07:36,333
what if what happened
last time happens again?

92
00:07:45,842 --> 00:07:48,053
I cannot promise you
it won't happen again.

93
00:07:49,721 --> 00:07:51,014
But I can promise you...

94
00:07:52,557 --> 00:07:54,684
that I will protect
you the best I can.

95
00:08:33,390 --> 00:08:34,057
<i>Third...</i>

96
00:08:34,391 --> 00:08:35,559
<i>you feel like</i>

97
00:08:35,851 --> 00:08:38,353
<i>you're always safe
whenever you're with him.</i>

98
00:08:39,354 --> 00:08:41,523
<i>It's like—your whole world stops.</i>

99
00:08:42,065 --> 00:08:43,024
<i>Like that.</i>

100
00:08:50,448 --> 00:08:51,424
Hey!

101
00:08:51,449 --> 00:08:52,784
It's already 7:45!

102
00:08:53,076 --> 00:08:54,719
Isn't our meeting at 8:00 a.m.?

103
00:08:54,744 --> 00:08:55,579
Let's go.

104
00:08:59,583 --> 00:09:01,293
Louie was wrong.

105
00:09:01,293 --> 00:09:02,544
Liar.

106
00:09:02,878 --> 00:09:04,546
Time didn't stop at all.

107
00:09:05,922 --> 00:09:06,464
Hey!

108
00:09:06,464 --> 00:09:07,507
Zeke, wait!

109
00:09:10,510 --> 00:09:11,386
Sigh.

110
00:09:11,678 --> 00:09:12,971
Exactly.

111
00:09:13,388 --> 00:09:15,348
And then, there's this too.

112
00:09:20,353 --> 00:09:22,981
Good morning,
Mr. and Mrs. Roswell.

113
00:09:22,981 --> 00:09:24,191
Good morning,
Mr. and Mrs. Roswell.

114
00:09:29,696 --> 00:09:30,822
Why are you still here?

115
00:09:31,740 --> 00:09:33,325
Excuse me, Mr. Roswell?

116
00:09:33,325 --> 00:09:35,327
I don't want to see your
fucking face anymore.

117
00:09:35,327 --> 00:09:38,788
You cannot fire an executive
without any concrete evidence

118
00:09:38,955 --> 00:09:40,336
on what you think I did.

119
00:09:46,004 --> 00:09:47,130
Zeke.

120
00:09:47,756 --> 00:09:49,925
The doctor said you're not
supposed to get stressed.

121
00:09:50,634 --> 00:09:51,593
I'll handle this.

122
00:09:52,093 --> 00:09:53,156
Leave it to me.

123
00:09:55,430 --> 00:09:56,598
Evidence!

124
00:09:57,933 --> 00:09:59,517
So it means,

125
00:10:00,060 --> 00:10:02,354
there's a possibility
that you're guilty.

126
00:10:04,898 --> 00:10:05,582
Okay.

127
00:10:05,607 --> 00:10:08,610
We are going to give you
another chance to tell us the truth.

128
00:10:10,295 --> 00:10:13,632
Were you the one who
stole the 100 million pesos?

129
00:10:13,657 --> 00:10:14,925
I will not answer that!

130
00:10:14,950 --> 00:10:16,257
This is harassment!

131
00:10:17,118 --> 00:10:18,828
I agree with the CFO.

132
00:10:21,790 --> 00:10:24,542
You cannot ask such questions
in front of the entire board.

133
00:10:24,542 --> 00:10:25,414
That's...

134
00:10:26,294 --> 00:10:27,379
unprofessional.

135
00:10:29,881 --> 00:10:31,591
What the fuck is she doing here?

136
00:10:42,352 --> 00:10:44,396
Let me remind all of you,

137
00:10:44,562 --> 00:10:47,649
that you all work for
Roswell Corporation.

138
00:10:48,692 --> 00:10:49,567
Roswell.

139
00:10:50,485 --> 00:10:53,363
And my husband owns the company.

140
00:10:54,072 --> 00:10:56,783
And by interfering
with his decisions,

141
00:10:56,783 --> 00:10:59,577
you are doing the
company a great disservice.

142
00:11:00,704 --> 00:11:03,456
You should be all
ashamed of yourselves.

143
00:11:05,625 --> 00:11:07,711
My husband just
got out of surgery.

144
00:11:11,923 --> 00:11:12,966
And as for you,

145
00:11:14,634 --> 00:11:17,554
I am giving you a lifetime
suspension, Ms.<i>"Sagwa."</i>

146
00:11:17,554 --> 00:11:18,805
It's Sigua! You can't!

147
00:11:18,805 --> 00:11:20,640
Yes, I can!

148
00:11:24,853 --> 00:11:27,522
Because I am the CEO's wife

149
00:11:27,772 --> 00:11:30,191
and I am giving you
a lifetime suspension.

150
00:11:31,735 --> 00:11:34,237
It doesn't violate
anything in the bylaws.

151
00:11:34,696 --> 00:11:35,697
That's my girl.

152
00:11:37,657 --> 00:11:39,784
But that's the
same as firing me!

153
00:11:39,784 --> 00:11:40,869
No, it's not.

154
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:44,289
You can't apply to
another company

155
00:11:44,289 --> 00:11:45,832
while you're working here.

156
00:11:45,915 --> 00:11:48,918
You're still required
to do your job as CFO

157
00:11:49,044 --> 00:11:52,297
without bonuses,
salary, which means...

158
00:11:52,672 --> 00:11:54,090
It's worse than firing you.

159
00:12:06,186 --> 00:12:09,272
Why are you laughing?
Nobody's joking.

160
00:12:14,110 --> 00:12:15,070
Alright, everyone.

161
00:12:15,153 --> 00:12:17,572
Let's stop wasting time
and get on with the meeting.

162
00:12:17,572 --> 00:12:18,445
Shall we?

163
00:12:19,491 --> 00:12:22,369
This meeting is exclusively
for board members.

164
00:12:23,161 --> 00:12:23,995
You're not needed here.

165
00:12:23,995 --> 00:12:26,706
This meeting is
about the toy industry,

166
00:12:27,332 --> 00:12:29,793
which I'm helping
your wife with, Ezekiel.

167
00:12:31,211 --> 00:12:33,546
Oh, so she's actually
going to help me.

168
00:12:33,922 --> 00:12:34,964
Oh, you don't know her.

169
00:12:35,298 --> 00:12:37,008
No, I know her.

170
00:12:37,133 --> 00:12:39,010
She's Fiona Stonehurst.

171
00:12:42,555 --> 00:12:43,515
Such an idiot.

172
00:12:47,185 --> 00:12:48,937
Why do you keep laughing?

173
00:12:48,937 --> 00:12:50,021
You're starting to worry me.

174
00:12:50,021 --> 00:12:50,867
Why?

175
00:12:51,189 --> 00:12:52,816
Is there something
wrong with being happy?

176
00:12:52,816 --> 00:12:53,650
No.

177
00:12:53,650 --> 00:12:54,943
So there's nothing wrong.

178
00:12:57,153 --> 00:12:59,989
Sorry to interrupt
your sweet moment.

179
00:13:00,490 --> 00:13:01,281
But...

180
00:13:02,367 --> 00:13:03,304
Shall we start?

181
00:13:04,119 --> 00:13:05,161
Sure. Go ahead.

182
00:13:09,374 --> 00:13:11,084
Sweet moments?

183
00:13:11,626 --> 00:13:13,545
Why does it feel like...

184
00:13:13,751 --> 00:13:16,754
like my heart is pounding?

185
00:13:39,946 --> 00:13:41,462
Hey!

186
00:13:42,198 --> 00:13:43,555
Oh no.

187
00:13:43,908 --> 00:13:45,577
Why isn't it pink anymore?

188
00:13:48,204 --> 00:13:50,390
And where are
all my Dollie dolls?

189
00:13:50,508 --> 00:13:51,759
Hi, Aemie.

190
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,293
That's your desk over there.

191
00:13:53,460 --> 00:13:54,641
Have a seat.

192
00:13:58,590 --> 00:14:00,758
Hey, why is my chair like this?

193
00:14:00,758 --> 00:14:02,719
It's like trip to Jerusalem.

194
00:14:03,887 --> 00:14:07,098
Aemie, I threw
out all of your trash.

195
00:14:07,724 --> 00:14:09,517
I wanted to make
it look a little more...

196
00:14:10,018 --> 00:14:10,923
professional?

197
00:14:12,187 --> 00:14:14,397
I dislike messy workplaces.

198
00:14:14,397 --> 00:14:15,423
Don't you?

199
00:14:22,614 --> 00:14:24,157
You're working here too?

200
00:14:25,575 --> 00:14:28,119
Why? There are
plenty of empty offices.

201
00:14:28,244 --> 00:14:30,246
Well, I thought it would
be nice if we could all

202
00:14:30,371 --> 00:14:31,431
work together.

203
00:14:31,456 --> 00:14:32,457
In one space.

204
00:14:32,665 --> 00:14:35,376
So I can make sure
you're doing things right.

205
00:14:36,336 --> 00:14:37,395
After all,

206
00:14:37,420 --> 00:14:40,131
I am your company's
supplier and partner

207
00:14:40,298 --> 00:14:43,718
for your new venture
into the toy industry.

208
00:15:03,863 --> 00:15:08,159
You'll be dead
soon, Aemie Roswell.

209
00:15:09,452 --> 00:15:10,703
Yaji.

210
00:15:16,417 --> 00:15:18,127
Who is this Yaji person?

211
00:15:19,420 --> 00:15:21,422
How does he know
I'm going to die?

212
00:15:23,716 --> 00:15:25,426
Is he a fortune teller?

213
00:15:27,887 --> 00:15:30,974
Oh no, what if
he's part of a cult?

214
00:15:32,517 --> 00:15:34,185
So creepy.

215
00:15:38,690 --> 00:15:39,774
So...

216
00:15:40,024 --> 00:15:41,109
uhm.

217
00:15:41,192 --> 00:15:42,318
Is Ezekiel coming?

218
00:15:43,528 --> 00:15:44,279
I don't know.

219
00:15:44,279 --> 00:15:45,947
You should've asked him, not me.

220
00:15:46,114 --> 00:15:47,173
Bitch?

221
00:15:47,448 --> 00:15:48,575
He's your husband.

222
00:15:49,617 --> 00:15:50,577
You should know.

223
00:16:04,132 --> 00:16:05,508
What the fuck happened here?

224
00:16:07,260 --> 00:16:08,636
And what the hell
are you doing here?

225
00:16:09,262 --> 00:16:10,238
Excuse me?

226
00:16:10,263 --> 00:16:12,098
The last time I was
here, everything was pink.

227
00:16:12,223 --> 00:16:13,933
And it was filled with dolls.

228
00:16:14,183 --> 00:16:15,141
Yeah.

229
00:16:16,978 --> 00:16:17,876
Zeke.

230
00:16:19,689 --> 00:16:21,482
Fiona did it.

231
00:16:22,734 --> 00:16:24,235
She changed the office.

232
00:16:24,485 --> 00:16:25,695
Look, Ezekiel.

233
00:16:26,029 --> 00:16:27,196
I'm sorry, but...

234
00:16:27,614 --> 00:16:29,243
you don't have a choice.

235
00:16:29,379 --> 00:16:30,422
I'm your partner now.

236
00:16:30,658 --> 00:16:34,037
In fact, I supply the
toys to your company.

237
00:16:34,829 --> 00:16:36,289
I did not agree to that.

238
00:16:36,748 --> 00:16:39,667
In fact, I don't like you
working with my wife.

239
00:16:39,667 --> 00:16:42,712
Well, your wife doesn't seem to
have a problem working with me.

240
00:16:43,755 --> 00:16:44,743
Right?

241
00:16:44,922 --> 00:16:45,720
Aemie?

242
00:16:54,849 --> 00:16:56,601
See, and in fact,

243
00:16:57,435 --> 00:16:59,145
I'm pretty sure I
did you guys a favor.

244
00:16:59,771 --> 00:17:01,105
I mean, look at this place.

245
00:17:02,315 --> 00:17:04,984
I know you like things
executive-looking.

246
00:17:04,984 --> 00:17:06,819
Stop acting like you
know what I want.

247
00:17:07,236 --> 00:17:10,323
What I don't like is how you
changed what my wife did.

248
00:17:14,202 --> 00:17:15,156
Let's go.

249
00:17:17,205 --> 00:17:18,265
Wait, wait, wait.

250
00:17:18,790 --> 00:17:22,377
Uhh, if you're heading home,
can I hitch a ride with you guys?

251
00:17:22,835 --> 00:17:24,420
My car broke down.

252
00:17:24,420 --> 00:17:25,335
- No.
- Sure.

253
00:17:32,381 --> 00:17:35,023
I just feel bad for
Fiona, you know?

254
00:17:35,473 --> 00:17:37,141
She already got
scolded, and then...

255
00:17:37,266 --> 00:17:38,768
her car broke down too.

256
00:17:39,310 --> 00:17:40,186
Besides.

257
00:17:40,853 --> 00:17:43,022
Maybe her attitude is so bad

258
00:17:43,022 --> 00:17:45,066
because nothing good
ever happens to her.

259
00:17:46,234 --> 00:17:47,777
We should take her home.

260
00:17:47,777 --> 00:17:50,446
Otherwise, she might end up
changing even more things in the office.

261
00:17:55,785 --> 00:17:56,624
Fine.

262
00:17:57,286 --> 00:17:58,249
Great.

263
00:17:58,996 --> 00:18:00,790
Maybe you wanna get
some food on the way home?

264
00:18:00,790 --> 00:18:01,974
Ezekiel?

265
00:18:01,999 --> 00:18:02,934
Are you hungry?

266
00:18:02,959 --> 00:18:03,459
Yeah.

267
00:18:03,459 --> 00:18:04,585
Honestly, I'm starving.

268
00:18:04,585 --> 00:18:04,919
- Wife,
- But I...

269
00:18:04,919 --> 00:18:06,921
I'm asking you, are you hungry?

270
00:18:10,299 --> 00:18:11,259
I'm not hungry, Dong.

271
00:18:11,509 --> 00:18:12,635
Okay, let's go then.

272
00:18:13,052 --> 00:18:13,960
Wait, but...

273
00:18:14,387 --> 00:18:15,680
I said I'm starving.

274
00:18:16,597 --> 00:18:17,807
The hell I care?

275
00:18:19,934 --> 00:18:22,228
Hey. Zeke, Zeke.

276
00:18:22,562 --> 00:18:25,273
Let's just hit the
drive-thru for Fiona

277
00:18:25,273 --> 00:18:28,693
because she looks really hungry.

278
00:18:35,533 --> 00:18:36,868
I am starving.

279
00:18:39,871 --> 00:18:40,531
Wait.

280
00:18:57,396 --> 00:19:00,107
This meeting is exclusively
for board members.

281
00:19:00,308 --> 00:19:02,852
This meeting is about
the toy industry...

282
00:19:03,603 --> 00:19:05,938
which I'm helping
your wife with, Ezekiel.

283
00:19:17,450 --> 00:19:18,374
Wife.

284
00:19:21,109 --> 00:19:23,039
Are you sure you're
okay working with Fiona?

285
00:19:24,665 --> 00:19:26,125
Uhhm.

286
00:19:28,377 --> 00:19:29,420
It's okay.

287
00:19:31,672 --> 00:19:34,926
She's annoying because she
threw away some of my Dollie dolls.

288
00:19:35,635 --> 00:19:37,553
But the book I read said,

289
00:19:37,553 --> 00:19:39,210
to "be professional," so...

290
00:19:39,722 --> 00:19:40,609
it's okay.

291
00:19:43,643 --> 00:19:44,609
Okay, then.

292
00:19:46,461 --> 00:19:47,121
Uhh.

293
00:19:47,146 --> 00:19:47,890
Zeke.

294
00:19:48,439 --> 00:19:51,567
Where did you go earlier before
you came back to the office?

295
00:19:54,257 --> 00:19:57,304
Lamperouge and I just dealt
with some business matters.

296
00:19:58,282 --> 00:19:59,200
How about you?

297
00:20:00,618 --> 00:20:01,499
Hmm?

298
00:20:01,619 --> 00:20:04,205
I saw your face earlier
when I entered the office.

299
00:20:05,289 --> 00:20:06,666
You seemed to
be deep in thought.

300
00:20:10,169 --> 00:20:12,380
Is something bothering you?

301
00:20:14,632 --> 00:20:15,624
Ah.

302
00:20:16,175 --> 00:20:17,101
That?

303
00:20:17,593 --> 00:20:18,531
Nothing, I was just...

304
00:20:18,556 --> 00:20:19,849
just thinking about something.

305
00:20:21,514 --> 00:20:22,289
About?

306
00:20:23,766 --> 00:20:24,684
Uhm...

307
00:20:26,326 --> 00:20:28,536
Maybe I shouldn't
tell him about Yaji yet.

308
00:20:29,939 --> 00:20:31,899
I don't even know who Yaji is.

309
00:20:34,902 --> 00:20:37,738
Yaji is actually a cute name.

310
00:20:39,699 --> 00:20:44,662
Ah, it's about, it's
about the Philippines.

311
00:20:45,204 --> 00:20:47,915
I want to help the
Philippines prosper!

312
00:21:01,721 --> 00:21:03,139
So boring.

313
00:21:04,056 --> 00:21:05,266
If I were a customer,

314
00:21:05,474 --> 00:21:06,809
I wouldn't buy these.

315
00:21:07,518 --> 00:21:08,304
Uhh.

316
00:21:08,728 --> 00:21:09,351
Well—

317
00:21:10,521 --> 00:21:12,148
Well, you're not a customer.

318
00:21:15,735 --> 00:21:18,321
Zeke, tell me if
these look boring.

319
00:21:37,214 --> 00:21:40,593
The designs I picked are
supposed to look mysterious.

320
00:21:40,760 --> 00:21:41,886
Like Zeke.

321
00:21:43,054 --> 00:21:44,492
<i>You know you love someone</i>

322
00:21:44,972 --> 00:21:46,766
<i>when you often compare them</i>

323
00:21:46,766 --> 00:21:49,060
<i>or relate them to different things.</i>

324
00:21:52,521 --> 00:21:53,189
No.

325
00:21:53,189 --> 00:21:54,078
Erase, erase.

326
00:21:54,207 --> 00:21:55,459
They're interesting.

327
00:21:56,359 --> 00:21:57,234
Hmm?

328
00:21:59,987 --> 00:22:00,929
Ezekiel.

329
00:22:01,739 --> 00:22:04,367
I think you should take a
look at these for consideration.

330
00:22:14,277 --> 00:22:15,153
Oh no!

331
00:22:15,920 --> 00:22:19,131
Those dolls look like they're
going to a Halloween party.

332
00:22:32,103 --> 00:22:33,226
You know what?

333
00:22:33,354 --> 00:22:34,897
I prefer my wife's choice.

334
00:22:38,734 --> 00:22:39,765
Yay!

335
00:22:39,986 --> 00:22:41,070
Yay!

336
00:23:04,301 --> 00:23:05,210
Huh?

337
00:23:06,929 --> 00:23:08,347
What is this Yaji thing?

338
00:23:09,348 --> 00:23:10,179
Why...

339
00:23:11,017 --> 00:23:13,602
why does he keep sending
me daily horoscopes?

340
00:23:15,763 --> 00:23:16,806
Let me reply.

341
00:23:18,274 --> 00:23:20,651
Mr. Yaji.

342
00:23:21,944 --> 00:23:24,822
Or, I don't know if
you're a miss?

343
00:23:26,407 --> 00:23:28,701
Could you...

344
00:23:29,452 --> 00:23:36,334
feng shui my and Zeke's house?

345
00:23:37,918 --> 00:23:40,129
And my mom's house too.

346
00:23:41,964 --> 00:23:45,301
So we can avoid...

347
00:23:46,802 --> 00:23:49,472
bad luck.

348
00:23:51,090 --> 00:23:52,008
Thank you.

349
00:23:54,852 --> 00:23:55,671
Ahh!

350
00:23:56,645 --> 00:23:57,730
P.S.

351
00:23:59,106 --> 00:24:01,609
Thank you for...

352
00:24:02,610 --> 00:24:04,737
sending my...

353
00:24:05,654 --> 00:24:08,532
daily horoscope for free.

354
00:24:09,700 --> 00:24:10,451
Send.

355
00:24:12,078 --> 00:24:12,929
Yes!

356
00:24:17,124 --> 00:24:17,875
Ezekiel?

357
00:24:19,752 --> 00:24:21,003
You gonna go for lunch?

358
00:24:24,090 --> 00:24:25,039
I'll join you.

359
00:24:26,842 --> 00:24:27,859
You can't.

360
00:24:28,219 --> 00:24:29,553
My wife and I have a date.

361
00:24:31,347 --> 00:24:33,474
We're going to have
lunch at her mother's place.

362
00:24:33,933 --> 00:24:34,867
Huh?

363
00:24:34,892 --> 00:24:35,804
Yay!

364
00:24:36,644 --> 00:24:38,395
I miss Mommy!

365
00:24:50,866 --> 00:24:51,801
Let's go?

366
00:24:51,826 --> 00:24:52,624
Come on.

367
00:24:55,996 --> 00:24:56,831
Enjoy.

368
00:25:23,399 --> 00:25:24,650
Ah, wait a second.

369
00:25:24,650 --> 00:25:26,193
Here, here's the juice.

370
00:25:27,987 --> 00:25:28,904
Here.

371
00:25:29,697 --> 00:25:30,614
Thank you.

372
00:25:36,745 --> 00:25:37,872
Mommy!

373
00:25:38,289 --> 00:25:39,665
Baby Ae!

374
00:25:40,583 --> 00:25:41,459
Zeke!

375
00:25:41,882 --> 00:25:43,627
Glad you stopped by again.

376
00:25:44,253 --> 00:25:45,593
Good afternoon, ma'am.

377
00:25:47,631 --> 00:25:49,800
Mommy, you have
so many customers.

378
00:25:49,967 --> 00:25:52,094
Dodong and I will help you sell.

379
00:25:53,846 --> 00:25:54,718
Huh?

380
00:25:54,889 --> 00:25:55,556
Really?

381
00:25:55,556 --> 00:25:56,365
Is that okay?

382
00:25:56,390 --> 00:25:57,421
Of course!

383
00:25:58,601 --> 00:25:59,367
What?

384
00:26:00,352 --> 00:26:01,039
Mm?

385
00:26:02,479 --> 00:26:03,179
Wait.

386
00:26:04,724 --> 00:26:07,310
You'll handle the grill,
and I'll take the orders.

387
00:26:13,824 --> 00:26:14,425
You don't want to?

388
00:26:14,450 --> 00:26:14,992
Okay, fine.

389
00:26:14,992 --> 00:26:17,244
You take the orders,
and I'll do the grilling.

390
00:26:18,329 --> 00:26:19,179
Hmm?

391
00:26:30,458 --> 00:26:31,834
Fine, I'll do it.

392
00:26:31,859 --> 00:26:35,015
Come on, go take the orders
so we can sell out all your...

393
00:26:35,512 --> 00:26:36,499
barbecue.

394
00:26:40,768 --> 00:26:41,562
Hurry.

395
00:26:42,102 --> 00:26:42,937
Go on.

396
00:26:44,313 --> 00:26:45,439
So you do want to.

397
00:26:46,106 --> 00:26:47,566
Oh no, not like that.

398
00:26:47,775 --> 00:26:48,943
Like this.

399
00:26:50,110 --> 00:26:51,278
There.

400
00:26:56,700 --> 00:26:58,035
Okay, guys!

401
00:26:58,786 --> 00:27:00,371
I have good news for all of you.

402
00:27:00,579 --> 00:27:03,499
Our barbecue is now
only 20 pesos per stick.

403
00:27:04,083 --> 00:27:07,002
And we have a special promo.

404
00:27:07,461 --> 00:27:13,234
For only 40 pesos,
it's buy one, get one.

405
00:27:13,259 --> 00:27:15,052
My daughter is really amazing.

406
00:27:15,177 --> 00:27:16,136
She's so good.

407
00:27:17,054 --> 00:27:18,681
Gosh, this girl is ridiculous.

408
00:27:19,306 --> 00:27:21,225
Hey, sir, you want to avail?

409
00:27:21,742 --> 00:27:22,184
How many?

410
00:27:22,184 --> 00:27:22,768
Three?

411
00:27:22,851 --> 00:27:23,894
There, make it five.

412
00:27:23,894 --> 00:27:25,145
She got that from me.

413
00:27:29,400 --> 00:27:30,265
Here you go, sir.

414
00:27:32,653 --> 00:27:33,779
Thank you!

415
00:27:33,862 --> 00:27:35,155
Hi, Aemie!

416
00:27:35,322 --> 00:27:36,907
Hey, Grace!

417
00:27:37,908 --> 00:27:39,493
Feels like I haven't
seen you in forever.

418
00:27:39,743 --> 00:27:41,996
I've been busy with school.

419
00:27:42,162 --> 00:27:45,833
The last time we saw
each other, you were still single.

420
00:27:46,041 --> 00:27:46,882
Yiee.

421
00:27:52,548 --> 00:27:54,091
I'd like five barbecue
sticks, please.

422
00:27:54,091 --> 00:27:55,070
Oh, okay.

423
00:27:55,509 --> 00:27:56,593
Five barbecue sticks.

424
00:27:57,428 --> 00:27:58,887
Dong, she wants
five barbecue sticks.

425
00:28:02,766 --> 00:28:03,892
Zeke, three betamax.

426
00:28:08,147 --> 00:28:09,481
Dong, five chicken intestines.

427
00:28:13,319 --> 00:28:15,070
Hey, Dong, four more betamax.

428
00:28:24,788 --> 00:28:27,207
Hey, Dong, six
more barbecue sticks.

429
00:29:13,962 --> 00:29:17,383
<i>You'll know you're definitely</i>
<i>in love with him</i>

430
00:29:18,175 --> 00:29:19,927
if, for you,

431
00:29:19,952 --> 00:29:23,497
he's the most handsome man ever.

432
00:29:31,947 --> 00:29:33,156
What are you staring at?

433
00:29:34,149 --> 00:29:34,909
Huh?

434
00:29:36,527 --> 00:29:39,321
Nothing, I was just
checking if you're getting tired.

435
00:29:41,323 --> 00:29:42,324
Don't get ahead of yourself.

436
00:29:42,324 --> 00:29:44,201
You might start
thinking that I'm thinking

437
00:29:44,201 --> 00:29:46,161
you're handsome even
when you're all sweaty.

438
00:29:48,622 --> 00:29:49,636
Okay.

439
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:53,335
Why are you smiling?

440
00:29:55,838 --> 00:29:57,172
Well, it's because...

441
00:29:59,716 --> 00:30:02,094
I love seeing my
special someone smile.

442
00:30:25,075 --> 00:30:26,493
Is this his special someone?

443
00:30:29,386 --> 00:30:31,206
How can a barbecue smile?

444
00:30:46,597 --> 00:30:47,425
Oh!

445
00:30:47,598 --> 00:30:48,659
Oh, it's your turn.

446
00:30:49,433 --> 00:30:50,309
You first.

447
00:30:50,309 --> 00:30:51,201
Hey, miss!

448
00:30:51,226 --> 00:30:52,167
My order.

449
00:30:52,478 --> 00:30:53,562
Wait, sis.

450
00:30:54,188 --> 00:30:54,938
Hold on.

451
00:30:55,355 --> 00:30:56,398
Why so mad?

452
00:30:57,024 --> 00:30:57,956
Here, sis.

453
00:30:59,693 --> 00:31:02,362
I hope your power gets cut off.

454
00:31:04,072 --> 00:31:06,450
What? But we're paying our bills.

455
00:31:07,159 --> 00:31:08,175
Over.

456
00:31:08,285 --> 00:31:09,369
Why so angry?

457
00:31:11,830 --> 00:31:12,598
Hey.

458
00:31:12,623 --> 00:31:14,374
Momo, do you see what I see?

459
00:31:15,417 --> 00:31:17,002
Of course, I'm not blind.

460
00:31:17,753 --> 00:31:18,754
Not blind?

461
00:31:19,087 --> 00:31:22,007
But I've been standing right
in front of you this whole time.

462
00:31:22,007 --> 00:31:23,884
And you still don't
see my worth.

463
00:31:27,095 --> 00:31:28,555
Hey, why are you here?

464
00:31:28,847 --> 00:31:30,098
Shouldn't you be at the office?

465
00:31:30,098 --> 00:31:30,557
Exactly.

466
00:31:30,557 --> 00:31:32,851
Oh, Cuz, we're on a date.

467
00:31:35,687 --> 00:31:36,464
Right, Dong?

468
00:31:37,898 --> 00:31:38,620
Yeah.

469
00:31:39,775 --> 00:31:40,459
Date?

470
00:31:40,484 --> 00:31:41,693
Oh, we're so in sync, Momo.

471
00:31:41,693 --> 00:31:43,487
Looks like we're
really soulmates.

472
00:31:43,987 --> 00:31:45,405
Soulmate, your face!

473
00:31:45,531 --> 00:31:46,990
- Go sit far away.
- There goes Momo again.

474
00:31:48,367 --> 00:31:50,202
- Charcoal flavored.
- Wow, seriously?

475
00:31:51,453 --> 00:31:53,997
Wife, are you
awake? I feel like...

476
00:31:54,248 --> 00:31:55,707
you're hiding something from me.

477
00:31:57,042 --> 00:32:00,212
Oh no! You know about
the last will and testament?

478
00:32:02,798 --> 00:32:04,508
Yes. But not that.

479
00:32:04,967 --> 00:32:08,136
I was beginning to think
you were getting threats...

480
00:32:09,513 --> 00:32:12,057
Threats? Maybe horoscopes.

481
00:32:12,307 --> 00:32:13,892
I don't have any enemies.

482
00:32:15,602 --> 00:32:19,356
Okay, I guess I was
afraid for no reason.

483
00:32:21,149 --> 00:32:24,319
So Dodong is scared of threats.

484
00:32:31,326 --> 00:32:33,537
What if I scare Dodong now?

485
00:32:36,673 --> 00:32:39,009
But I'm already so comfortable in my bed.

486
00:32:40,794 --> 00:32:42,462
Oh, I know.

487
00:32:42,963 --> 00:32:45,215
I'll just text him the threats.

488
00:32:51,555 --> 00:32:55,684
This is a threat. I can
see you Ezekiel Roswell.

489
00:32:55,892 --> 00:32:58,729
You should be afraid now! RAWR!

490
00:33:02,441 --> 00:33:03,527
P.S.

491
00:33:04,318 --> 00:33:06,570
This is not Aemie.

492
00:33:13,285 --> 00:33:14,536
I hope he gets scared.

493
00:33:20,167 --> 00:33:21,355
Oh no.

494
00:33:21,835 --> 00:33:23,211
He didn't even get scared.

495
00:33:23,211 --> 00:33:24,046
Unfair.

496
00:33:27,382 --> 00:33:29,009
Why weren't you scared, Zeke?

497
00:33:31,970 --> 00:33:34,168
Why would I?

498
00:33:37,976 --> 00:33:39,936
I thought you were
afraid of threats?

499
00:33:45,442 --> 00:33:46,860
Insane!

500
00:33:48,487 --> 00:33:49,696
So now I'm insane?

501
00:33:57,829 --> 00:33:59,039
Who's this?

502
00:34:12,094 --> 00:34:14,596
Dong thinks he's a smartass!

503
00:34:15,389 --> 00:34:16,973
You think you can scare me?

504
00:34:17,224 --> 00:34:18,238
Nope!

505
00:34:21,019 --> 00:34:21,978
Suit yourself.

506
00:34:23,689 --> 00:34:24,824
I'm getting sleepy.

507
00:34:34,741 --> 00:34:35,637
Wife.

508
00:34:35,909 --> 00:34:36,326
Dong.

509
00:34:36,326 --> 00:34:38,620
Have you already met
with the staff about lunch?

510
00:34:38,912 --> 00:34:41,957
Oh, not yet, but it's
scheduled for next week.

511
00:34:42,165 --> 00:34:44,376
Fiona and I just
need to meet first.

512
00:34:46,211 --> 00:34:47,354
Oh, there she is.

513
00:34:47,379 --> 00:34:48,271
Hi, Fiona.

514
00:34:48,296 --> 00:34:49,285
- Hi.
- Shall we start?

515
00:34:49,673 --> 00:34:51,633
I just need to speak
to Ezekiel first.

516
00:34:52,300 --> 00:34:53,043
Okay.

517
00:34:55,095 --> 00:34:56,029
Speak.

518
00:34:56,054 --> 00:34:56,988
In private.

519
00:34:57,013 --> 00:34:57,902
I hope.

520
00:35:01,435 --> 00:35:03,895
Now she's asking for privacy.

521
00:35:03,895 --> 00:35:06,189
It's not like Dong's
office is a public place.

522
00:35:29,004 --> 00:35:30,464
I should call Cai.

523
00:35:38,555 --> 00:35:39,639
Oh my gosh.

524
00:35:46,438 --> 00:35:47,397
Fine.

525
00:35:49,524 --> 00:35:50,567
Hi, Cai!

526
00:35:50,776 --> 00:35:51,818
Hi, Aemie!

527
00:35:51,818 --> 00:35:52,778
You called?

528
00:35:53,028 --> 00:35:53,612
Nothing.

529
00:35:53,612 --> 00:35:54,988
I just missed you.

530
00:35:54,988 --> 00:35:57,032
You weren't there when
we went to the beach.

531
00:35:57,032 --> 00:35:58,450
We had so much fun.

532
00:35:58,909 --> 00:36:01,578
Sorry, I've been kinda busy lately.

533
00:36:01,578 --> 00:36:03,830
I'm looking for something.

534
00:36:04,414 --> 00:36:05,265
Oh, really?

535
00:36:05,290 --> 00:36:06,516
What are you looking for?

536
00:36:06,541 --> 00:36:07,709
Want me to help?

537
00:36:08,084 --> 00:36:09,377
Ah, no need.

538
00:36:09,377 --> 00:36:10,378
Ah, I can handle it.

539
00:36:11,004 --> 00:36:12,839
Oh, by the way, how's work?

540
00:36:13,131 --> 00:36:15,759
I heard you're entering
the toy industry.

541
00:36:16,176 --> 00:36:17,052
Oh, yeah.

542
00:36:17,052 --> 00:36:18,553
We're launching
within the month.

543
00:36:18,553 --> 00:36:19,780
You should come.

544
00:36:19,805 --> 00:36:21,573
- Huh?
- Yeah, of course.

545
00:36:21,598 --> 00:36:23,058
I'll be there with my dad.

546
00:36:23,058 --> 00:36:24,434
You know my dad.

547
00:36:24,935 --> 00:36:27,020
If it's business,
he's always present.

548
00:36:27,187 --> 00:36:29,689
Alright, I need to go to
class, Aemie girl.

549
00:36:30,023 --> 00:36:30,565
Okay.

550
00:36:30,565 --> 00:36:31,824
Alright, bye-bye. Take care.

551
00:36:31,900 --> 00:36:33,193
Love, love.

552
00:36:51,586 --> 00:36:52,629
Exciting.

553
00:36:53,046 --> 00:36:55,340
I wonder what
Mr. Ferrer looks like.

554
00:36:55,715 --> 00:36:56,716
Do you think he's handsome?

555
00:37:00,487 --> 00:37:02,572
Maybe I should bring Mommy.

556
00:37:02,597 --> 00:37:04,683
So she can have a love team.

557
00:37:05,308 --> 00:37:07,352
Because as far as I
know, Cai's dad is single.

558
00:37:10,230 --> 00:37:11,039
Right.

